    {
      "parameters": {
        "sendTo": "={{ $json.lead_email }}",
        "subject": "What our Nashville clients are finding in their homes",
        "emailType": "html",
        "message": "<p>Hi {{ $json.lead_name }},</p>\n\n<p>I wanted to follow up with a quick note — and share a few real stories from Nashville-area clients we've worked with recently (all details anonymized, of course).</p>\n\n<p>These aren't horror stories. They're just eye-opening examples of what testing actually reveals:</p>\n\n<hr style=\"border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 20px 0;\">\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #2E7D32;\">Story 1: Mold After a \"Minor\" Leak</h3>\n<p>A family in Brentwood had a small roof leak repaired two years ago. The repair looked fine. But after their daughter started experiencing persistent respiratory issues, they called us. Our inspection found elevated mold spore counts in three rooms — traced to moisture trapped behind drywall during the original repair. Early intervention saved thousands in potential remediation costs and, more importantly, identified the source of their daughter's symptoms.</p>\n\n<hr style=\"border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 20px 0;\">\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #2E7D32;\">Story 2: VOCs in New Construction</h3>\n<p>A couple moved into a newly built home in Franklin and noticed headaches and fatigue within weeks. Our air quality test found significantly elevated levels of formaldehyde and other volatile organic compounds (VOCs) off-gassing from new flooring, cabinets, and paint. With targeted ventilation and a few product swaps, their air quality improved within 30 days.</p>\n\n<hr style=\"border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 20px 0;\">\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #2E7D32;\">Story 3: EMF Near a Cell Tower</h3>\n<p>A small business owner near a major intersection was concerned about a new cell tower installed 200 feet from their office. Our EMF testing provided a detailed map of RF exposure levels throughout the space — most were within safe ranges, but we identified two workstation areas with elevated readings and recommended simple shielding solutions.</p>\n\n<hr style=\"border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eee; margin: 20px 0;\">\n\n<p>The common thread? <strong>These issues were invisible until tested.</strong> No smell, no obvious sign — just subtle health impacts that took months to connect to their environment.</p>\n\n<p>If any of this resonates with your situation, I'd love to schedule a quick call or consultation to talk through what testing might make sense for your {{ $json.lead_type_label }}.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center; margin: 30px 0;\">\n  <a href=\"YOUR_APPTOTAL_BOOKING_LINK\" style=\"background-color: #2E7D32; color: white; padding: 14px 28px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 16px;\">Book a Consultation</a>\n</p>\n\n<p>Warmly,<br>\n<strong>Martine Davis</strong><br>\nIndoor Environmental Testing Inc.<br>\nNashville, TN | Madison, WI</p>",
        "options": {
          "replyTo": "martine@indoorenvironmentaltesting.com"
        }
      },
